1.wrap my mind around ...

美式：I can’t wrap my mind around why he quit such a good job.
英式：I just can’t get my head around the new regulations.

A: What makes you get up so early every day?
B: Ever since I came back from Italy, I’ve been waking up early because of jet lag.
A: Looks like the jet lag is making you healthier. 
		。。。。What time do you usually get up?


Yeah, that’s true. I’m wondering if I should try to keep this habit going — do you think it’s worth it?
It actually makes me feel better during the day. Do you notice a difference when you wake up early vs. late?

Maybe I should thank jet lag for fixing my sleep schedule — has that ever happened to you?

has that ever happened to you?。。


2.it just stuck.
I tried waking up early during the pandemic, and it just stuck.

3.pick up
	I picked up yoga during college, and it just stuck.
	I picked up running since the pandemic, and it just stuck.
	I picked up the habit of waking up early because of jet lag, and it just stuck.

时间的奥秘不在于它的长短，而在于你如何用经历为它标注深度
给每段时间起一个名字


Polished English Version
I wasted too much time in the past—
time that could have been spent doing meaningful things,
time that could have created memories worth cherishing.
But I let it slip away and didn’t do much that truly mattered.
Still, what’s past is past.
I shouldn’t dwell on regret or sunk costs.
Instead, I should learn from my mistakes and face the future head-on.
I still have plenty of time ahead of me,
and my past failures only make me value that time even more.


